{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"The brilliant playwright, Adrienne Kennedy,"},{"time":4000,"text":"wrote a volume called"},{"time":6000,"text":"\"People Who Led to My Plays.\""},{"time":8000,"text":"And if I were to write a volume,"},{"time":10000,"text":"it would be called,"},{"time":12000,"text":"\"Artists Who Have Led My Exhibitions\""},{"time":14000,"text":"because my work,"},{"time":16000,"text":"in understanding art and in understanding culture,"},{"time":19000,"text":"has come by following artists,"},{"time":22000,"text":"by looking at what artists mean"},{"time":25000,"text":"and what they do and who they are."},{"time":28000,"text":"J.J. from \"Good Times,\""},{"time":30000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":33000,"text":"significant to many people of course"},{"time":35000,"text":"because of \"Dy-no-mite,\""},{"time":37000,"text":"but perhaps more significant"},{"time":39000,"text":"as the first, really, black artist"},{"time":42000,"text":"on primetime TV."},{"time":45000,"text":"Jean-Michel Basquiat,"},{"time":47000,"text":"important to me because [he was]"},{"time":49000,"text":"the first black artist in real time"},{"time":52000,"text":"that showed me the possibility of"},{"time":54000,"text":"who and what I was about to enter into."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57000,"text":"My overall project is about art --"},{"time":60000,"text":"specifically, about black artists --"},{"time":62000,"text":"very generally"},{"time":64000,"text":"about the way in which art"},{"time":66000,"text":"can change the way we think"},{"time":68000,"text":"about culture and ourselves."},{"time":71000,"text":"My interest is in artists"},{"time":73000,"text":"who understand and rewrite history,"},{"time":76000,"text":"who think about themselves"},{"time":78000,"text":"within the narrative"},{"time":80000,"text":"of the larger world of art,"},{"time":82000,"text":"but who have created new places"},{"time":84000,"text":"for us to see and understand."},{"time":87000,"text":"I'm showing two artists here, \nGlenn Ligon and Kara Walker,"},{"time":90000,"text":"two of many who really form for me"},{"time":93000,"text":"the essential questions that I wanted to bring"},{"time":96000,"text":"as a curator to the world."},{"time":98000,"text":"I was interested in the idea"},{"time":101000,"text":"of why and how"},{"time":103000,"text":"I could create a new story,"},{"time":106000,"text":"a new narrative in art history"},{"time":108000,"text":"and a new narrative in the world."},{"time":110000,"text":"And to do this, I knew"},{"time":112000,"text":"that I had to see the way in which artists work,"},{"time":115000,"text":"understand the artist's studio"},{"time":117000,"text":"as a laboratory,"},{"time":119000,"text":"imagine, then,"},{"time":121000,"text":"reinventing the museum as a think tank"},{"time":124000,"text":"and looking at the exhibition"},{"time":127000,"text":"as the ultimate white paper -- asking questions,"},{"time":130000,"text":"providing the space"},{"time":132000,"text":"to look and to think about answers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135000,"text":"In 1994,"},{"time":137000,"text":"when I was a curator at the Whitney Museum,"},{"time":139000,"text":"I made an exhibition called Black Male."},{"time":141000,"text":"It looked at the intersection"},{"time":143000,"text":"of race and gender"},{"time":145000,"text":"in contemporary American art."},{"time":147000,"text":"It sought to express"},{"time":149000,"text":"the ways in which art"},{"time":151000,"text":"could provide a space for dialogue --"},{"time":153000,"text":"complicated dialogue,"},{"time":155000,"text":"dialogue with many, many points of entry --"},{"time":158000,"text":"and how the museum could be the space"},{"time":160000,"text":"for this contest of ideas."},{"time":162000,"text":"This exhibition included"},{"time":164000,"text":"over 20 artists"},{"time":166000,"text":"of various ages and races,"},{"time":168000,"text":"but all looking at black masculinity"},{"time":171000,"text":"from a very particular point of view."},{"time":177000,"text":"What was significant about this exhibition"},{"time":180000,"text":"is the way in which"},{"time":182000,"text":"it engaged me in my role"},{"time":185000,"text":"as a curator, as a catalyst,"},{"time":187000,"text":"for this dialogue."},{"time":189000,"text":"One of the things that happened"},{"time":191000,"text":"very distinctly in the course of this exhibition"},{"time":193000,"text":"is I was confronted with the idea"},{"time":195000,"text":"of how powerful images can be"},{"time":197000,"text":"in people's understanding \nof themselves and each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"I'm showing you two works, one on the right by Leon Golub,"},{"time":203000,"text":"one on the left by Robert Colescott."},{"time":206000,"text":"And in the course of the exhibition --"},{"time":208000,"text":"which was contentious, controversial"},{"time":210000,"text":"and ultimately, for me,"},{"time":212000,"text":"life-changing"},{"time":214000,"text":"in my sense of what art could be --"},{"time":216000,"text":"a woman came up to me on the gallery floor"},{"time":219000,"text":"to express her concern about the nature"},{"time":222000,"text":"of how powerful images could be"},{"time":224000,"text":"and how we understood each other."},{"time":226000,"text":"And she pointed to the work on the left"},{"time":228000,"text":"to tell me how problematic this image was,"},{"time":230000,"text":"as it related, for her, to the idea of"},{"time":233000,"text":"how black people had been represented."},{"time":236000,"text":"And she pointed to the image on the right"},{"time":238000,"text":"as an example, to me, of the kind of dignity"},{"time":241000,"text":"that needed to be portrayed"},{"time":243000,"text":"to work against those images in the media."},{"time":245000,"text":"She then assigned these works racial identities,"},{"time":248000,"text":"basically saying to me that the work on the right,"},{"time":250000,"text":"clearly, was made by a black artist,"},{"time":252000,"text":"the work on the left, clearly, by a white artist,"},{"time":254000,"text":"when, in effect,"},{"time":256000,"text":"that was the opposite case:"},{"time":258000,"text":"Bob Colescott, African-American artist;"},{"time":260000,"text":"Leon Golub, a white artist."},{"time":262000,"text":"The point of that for me was"},{"time":264000,"text":"to say -- in that space, in that moment --"},{"time":267000,"text":"that I really, more than anything,"},{"time":269000,"text":"wanted to understand"},{"time":271000,"text":"how images could work, how images did work,"},{"time":274000,"text":"and how artists provided"},{"time":276000,"text":"a space bigger than one"},{"time":278000,"text":"that we could imagine in our day-to-day lives"},{"time":280000,"text":"to work through these images."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283000,"text":"Fast-forward and I end up in Harlem;"},{"time":286000,"text":"home for many of black America,"},{"time":289000,"text":"very much the psychic heart"},{"time":292000,"text":"of the black experience,"},{"time":294000,"text":"really the place where the Harlem Renaissance existed."},{"time":298000,"text":"Harlem now, sort of explaining"},{"time":301000,"text":"and thinking of itself in this part of the century,"},{"time":304000,"text":"looking both backwards and forwards ..."},{"time":306000,"text":"I always say Harlem is an interesting community"},{"time":308000,"text":"because, unlike many other places,"},{"time":310000,"text":"it thinks of itself in the past, present"},{"time":312000,"text":"and the future simultaneously;"},{"time":314000,"text":"no one speaks of it just in the now."},{"time":316000,"text":"It's always what it was and what it can be."},{"time":319000,"text":"And, in thinking about that,"},{"time":321000,"text":"then my second project, the second question I ask is:"},{"time":323000,"text":"Can a museum"},{"time":325000,"text":"be a catalyst in a community?"},{"time":327000,"text":"Can a museum house artists"},{"time":329000,"text":"and allow them to be change agents"},{"time":331000,"text":"as communities rethink themselves?"},{"time":334000,"text":"This is Harlem, actually, on January 20th,"},{"time":337000,"text":"thinking about itself in a very wonderful way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341000,"text":"So I work now at The Studio Museum in Harlem,"},{"time":343000,"text":"thinking about exhibitions there,"},{"time":345000,"text":"thinking about what it means to"},{"time":347000,"text":"discover art's possibility."},{"time":349000,"text":"Now, what does this mean to some of you?"},{"time":351000,"text":"In some cases, I know that many of you"},{"time":354000,"text":"are involved in cross-cultural dialogues,"},{"time":356000,"text":"you're involved in ideas of creativity and innovation."},{"time":359000,"text":"Think about the place that artists can play in that --"},{"time":362000,"text":"that is the kind of incubation and advocacy"},{"time":365000,"text":"that I work towards, in working with young, black artists."},{"time":368000,"text":"Think about artists, not as content providers,"},{"time":370000,"text":"though they can be brilliant at that,"},{"time":372000,"text":"but, again, as real catalysts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376000,"text":"The Studio Museum was founded in the late 60s."},{"time":379000,"text":"And I bring this up because it's important to locate"},{"time":382000,"text":"this practice in history."},{"time":384000,"text":"To look at 1968,"},{"time":386000,"text":"in the incredible historic moment that it is,"},{"time":388000,"text":"and think of the arc that has happened since then,"},{"time":391000,"text":"to think of the possibilities that we are all"},{"time":394000,"text":"privileged to stand in today"},{"time":396000,"text":"and imagine that this museum"},{"time":398000,"text":"that came out of a moment of great protest"},{"time":400000,"text":"and one that was so much about"},{"time":402000,"text":"examining the history and the legacy"},{"time":404000,"text":"of important African-American artists"},{"time":407000,"text":"to the history of art in this country"},{"time":409000,"text":"like Jacob Lawrence, Norman Lewis,"},{"time":411000,"text":"Romare Bearden."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413000,"text":"And then, of course,"},{"time":415000,"text":"to bring us to today."},{"time":417000,"text":"In 1975, Muhammad Ali"},{"time":419000,"text":"gave a lecture at Harvard University."},{"time":421000,"text":"After his lecture, a student got up and said to him,"},{"time":424000,"text":"\"Give us a poem.\""},{"time":426000,"text":"And Mohammed Ali said, \"Me, we.\""},{"time":428000,"text":"A profound statement about the individual and the community."},{"time":431000,"text":"The space in which now,"},{"time":433000,"text":"in my project of discovery, of thinking about artists,"},{"time":436000,"text":"of trying to define"},{"time":438000,"text":"what might be"},{"time":440000,"text":"black art cultural movement of the 21st century."},{"time":443000,"text":"What that might mean"},{"time":445000,"text":"for cultural movements all over this moment,"},{"time":448000,"text":"the \"me, we\" seems"},{"time":450000,"text":"incredibly prescient"},{"time":452000,"text":"totally important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454000,"text":"To this end,"},{"time":456000,"text":"the specific project that has made this possible for me"},{"time":459000,"text":"is a series of exhibitions,"},{"time":461000,"text":"all titled with an F --"},{"time":463000,"text":"Freestyle, Frequency and Flow --"},{"time":465000,"text":"which have set out to discover"},{"time":467000,"text":"and define"},{"time":469000,"text":"the young, black artists working in this moment"},{"time":472000,"text":"who I feel strongly"},{"time":474000,"text":"will continue to work over the next many years."},{"time":477000,"text":"This series of exhibitions"},{"time":479000,"text":"was made specifically"},{"time":481000,"text":"to try and question"},{"time":483000,"text":"the idea of what it would mean"},{"time":485000,"text":"now, at this point in history,"},{"time":487000,"text":"to see art as a catalyst;"},{"time":490000,"text":"what it means now, at this point in history,"},{"time":492000,"text":"as we define and redefine culture,"},{"time":495000,"text":"black culture specifically in my case,"},{"time":497000,"text":"but culture generally."},{"time":499000,"text":"I named this group of artists"},{"time":501000,"text":"around an idea, which I put out there"},{"time":504000,"text":"called post-black,"},{"time":506000,"text":"really meant to define them"},{"time":508000,"text":"as artists who came and start their work now,"},{"time":511000,"text":"looking back at history but start in this moment, historically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515000,"text":"It is really in this sense of discovery"},{"time":518000,"text":"that I have a new set of questions that I'm asking."},{"time":521000,"text":"This new set of questions is:"},{"time":523000,"text":"What does it mean, right now,"},{"time":525000,"text":"to be African-American in America?"},{"time":528000,"text":"What can artwork say about this?"},{"time":531000,"text":"Where can a museum exist"},{"time":534000,"text":"as the place for us all"},{"time":537000,"text":"to have this conversation?"},{"time":539000,"text":"Really, most exciting about this"},{"time":541000,"text":"is thinking about the energy and the excitement"},{"time":544000,"text":"that young artists can bring."},{"time":546000,"text":"Their works for me are about,"},{"time":548000,"text":"not always just simply"},{"time":550000,"text":"about the aesthetic innovation"},{"time":552000,"text":"that their minds imagine, that their visions create"},{"time":555000,"text":"and put out there in the world,"},{"time":557000,"text":"but more, perhaps, importantly,"},{"time":559000,"text":"through the excitement of the community"},{"time":561000,"text":"that they create as important voices"},{"time":564000,"text":"that would allow us right now to understand our situation,"},{"time":567000,"text":"as well as in the future."},{"time":569000,"text":"I am continually amazed"},{"time":572000,"text":"by the way in which"},{"time":574000,"text":"the subject of race"},{"time":576000,"text":"can take itself in many places"},{"time":579000,"text":"that we don't imagine it should be."},{"time":581000,"text":"I am always amazed"},{"time":584000,"text":"by the way in which artists are willing"},{"time":586000,"text":"to do that in their work."},{"time":588000,"text":"It is why I look to art."},{"time":590000,"text":"It's why I ask questions of art."},{"time":592000,"text":"It is why I make exhibitions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595000,"text":"Now, this exhibition, as I said,"},{"time":597000,"text":"40 young artists done over the course of eight years,"},{"time":600000,"text":"and for me it's about considering the implications."},{"time":604000,"text":"It's considering the implications of"},{"time":606000,"text":"what this generation has to say to the rest of us."},{"time":609000,"text":"It's considering what it means for these artists"},{"time":612000,"text":"to be both out in the world as their work travels,"},{"time":614000,"text":"but in their communities"},{"time":616000,"text":"as people who are seeing and thinking"},{"time":619000,"text":"about the issues that face us."},{"time":622000,"text":"It's also about thinking about"},{"time":624000,"text":"the creative spirit and nurturing it,"},{"time":626000,"text":"and imagining, particularly in urban America,"},{"time":628000,"text":"about the nurturing of the spirit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631000,"text":"Now, where, perhaps, does this end up right now?"},{"time":634000,"text":"For me, it is about re-imagining"},{"time":637000,"text":"this cultural discourse in an international context."},{"time":640000,"text":"So the last iteration of this project"},{"time":643000,"text":"has been called Flow,"},{"time":645000,"text":"with the idea now of creating"},{"time":647000,"text":"a real network"},{"time":649000,"text":"of artists around the world;"},{"time":651000,"text":"really looking, not so much"},{"time":653000,"text":"from Harlem and out, but looking across,"},{"time":656000,"text":"and Flow looked at artists all born on the continent of Africa."},{"time":659000,"text":"And as many of us think about that continent"},{"time":662000,"text":"and think about what if means"},{"time":664000,"text":"to us all in the 21st century,"},{"time":666000,"text":"I have begun that looking"},{"time":668000,"text":"through artists, through artworks,"},{"time":670000,"text":"and imagining what they can tell us about the future,"},{"time":673000,"text":"what they tell us about our future,"},{"time":676000,"text":"and what they create in their sense of"},{"time":679000,"text":"offering us this great possibility of watching"},{"time":682000,"text":"that continent emerge as part"},{"time":684000,"text":"of our bigger dialogue."},{"time":686000,"text":"So, what do I discover"}]},{"cues":[{"time":688000,"text":"when I look at artworks?"},{"time":690000,"text":"What do I think about"},{"time":692000,"text":"when I think about art?"},{"time":694000,"text":"I feel like the privilege I've had as a curator"},{"time":696000,"text":"is not just the discovery of new works,"},{"time":699000,"text":"the discovery of exciting works."},{"time":701000,"text":"But, really, it has been"},{"time":703000,"text":"what I've discovered about myself"},{"time":705000,"text":"and what I can offer"},{"time":707000,"text":"in the space of an exhibition,"},{"time":709000,"text":"to talk about beauty, to talk about power,"},{"time":712000,"text":"to talk about ourselves,"},{"time":714000,"text":"and to talk and speak to each other."},{"time":717000,"text":"That's what makes me get up every day"},{"time":720000,"text":"and want to think about"},{"time":722000,"text":"this generation of black artists and artists around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725000,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}